"We believe that it is a small number of students to cause these inconveniences, and if they intend to protest, Americans have the right to do so peacefully and in compliance with the law," said the White House spokesman, Karine Jean-Pierre. During a comizio in Wisconsin, Biden's challenger, his predecessor Donald Trump, instead called "a beautiful thing to look at" the eviction of Columbia students, who had occupied Hamilton Hall.&nbsp;
